    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nReading buffer/tab/window-local variables¹ (`b:/v:/t:/w:`), any values set to `v:null` are returned as `vim.NIL`, which is \"truthy\" in Lua and may not be convenient in some cases.\n\n\n1: (This applies to any vimscript variable, but the \"scoped\" dicts are the most relevant for Lua)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nvim_get_var()` gains a `{ luanil: boolean }` parameter, similar to `vim.json.decode`.\n\n### Related\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40159",
